    "The metrics of validity, uniqueness, and novelty that we've used for PV-to-SMILES generation are defined as follows:",
    "For MoleculeNet downstream tasks and the DILI classification task that only provide SMILES data, we utilized only the SMILES encoder part of the model (Supplementary Fig. 1c).",
    "After the input molecule is encoded with the SMILES encoder, we pass the feature of the [CLS] S token through a classification/regression head to get an output.",
    "The classification/regression head consists of MLP with one hidden layer.",
    "We fine-tuned our model with the given training set and get a checkpoint with the lowest loss on the validation set, and recorded that checkpoint's performance on the test set."
